Field.Name: SUCCESS
Field.Description: Successful operation

Field.Name: MISC_ERROR_TOTAL
Field.Description: The operation has not be executed in total

Field.Name: MISC_ERROR_PARTIAL
Field.Description: The operation has been executed only partial

Field.Name: PERMISSON_ERROR
Field.Description: Password required

Field.Name: PASSWORD_ERROR
Field.Description: Password is wrong

Field.Name: REGION_NOT_FOUND_ERROR
Field.Description: Memory region not available for the actual tag

Field.Name: OP_NOT_POSSIBLE_ERROR
Field.Description: Operation not supported by the actual tag

Field.Name: OUT_OF_RANGE_ERROR
Field.Description: Addressed memory not available for the actual tag

Field.Name: NO_IDENTIFIER
Field.Description: The operation cannot be executed because no tag or code was inside the range of the AutoID Device or the tag or code has been moved out of the range during execution

Field.Name: MULTIPLE_IDENTIFIERS
Field.Description: Multiple tags or codes have been selected, but the command can only be used with a single tag or code

Field.Name: READ_ERROR
Field.Description: The tag or code exists and has a valid format, but there was a problem reading the data (e.g. still CRC error after maximum number of retries)

Field.Name: DECODING_ERROR
Field.Description: The (optical) code or plain text has too many failures and cannot be detected

Field.Name: MATCH_ERROR
Field.Description: The code doesn’t match the given target value

Field.Name: CODE_NOT_SUPPORTED
Field.Description: The code format is not supported by the AutoID Device

Field.Name: WRITE_ERROR
Field.Description: The tag exists, but there was a problem writing the data

Field.Name: NOT_SUPPORTED_BY_DEVICE
Field.Description: The command or a parameter combination is not supported by the AutoID Device

Field.Name: NOT_SUPPORTED_BY_TAG
Field.Description: The command or a parameter combination is not supported by the tag

Field.Name: DEVICE_NOT_READY
Field.Description: The AutoID Device is in a state not ready to execute the command

Field.Name: INVALID_CONFIGURATION
Field.Description: The AutoID Device configuration is not valid

Field.Name: RF_COMMUNICATION_ERROR
Field.Description: This error indicates that there is a general error in the communication between the transponder and the reader

Field.Name: DEVICE_FAULT
Field.Description: The AutoID Device has a hardware fault

Field.Name: TAG_HAS_LOW_BATTERY
Field.Description: The battery of the (active) tag is low

UADataType.Description: Result values of an AutoID Identifier access

Field.Name: CodeType
Field.Description: Defines the format of Identifier as string

Field.Name: Identifier
Field.Description: The AutoID Identifier (e.g. a code or a transponder) which was accessed by a command

Field.Name: Timestamp
Field.Description: The point of time the AutoID Identifier was accessed by the command.

UADataType.Description: Additional result values of an Rfid Transponder access

Field.Name: CodeTypeRWData
Field.Description: Defines the format of RWData as string

Field.Name: RWData
Field.Description: The user data which was written to / was read from the Rfid Transponder by the command

Field.Name: Antenna
Field.Description: The antenna by which the transponder was accessed by the command

Field.Name: CurrentPowerLevel
Field.Description: The power level with which the transponder was accessed by the command

Field.Name: PC
Field.Description: The Protocol Control Word of the transponder accessed by the command

Field.Name: Polarization
Field.Description: The polarization with which the last transponder was accessed by the command

Field.Name: Strength
Field.Description: The Rssi value with which the transponder was accessed by the command

Field.Name: Timestamp
Field.Description: Optional

Field.Name: DilutionOfPrecision
Field.Description: Optional

Field.Name: UsefulPrecision
Field.Description: Optional

Field.Name: Antenna
Field.Description: Returns the number of the antenna which detects the RFID tag first.

Field.Name: Strength
Field.Description: Returns the signal strength (RSSI) of the transponder. Higher values indicate a better strength.

Field.Name: Timestamp
Field.Description: Timestamp in UtcTime

Field.Name: CurrentPowerLevel
Field.Description: Returns the current power level (unit according to parameter settings)

Field.Name: CodeType
Field.Description: Defines the format of the ScanData as string.

Field.Name: ScanData
Field.Description: Holds the information about the detected objects e.g. the detected transponders.

Field.Name: Timestamp
Field.Description: Timestamp of the ScanResult creation.

Field.Name: Location
Field.Description: Returns the location of the object detection.

Field.Name: ImageId
Field.Description: NodeId of the original scan image file object used for this scan result

Field.Name: Quality
Field.Description: Returns the probability of correct decoding

Field.Name: Position
Field.Description: Returns the position of the text within the image

Field.Name: Font
Field.Description: Returns the font name used for decoding

Field.Name: DecodingTime
Field.Description: Returns the required decoding time

Field.Name: Grade
Field.Description: Returns the quality of the 1D/2D code

Field.Name: Position
Field.Description: Returns the position of the text within the image

Field.Name: Sighting
Field.Description: Returns additional information on the RFID-related properties of the scan event
